11/13/2023,748.507(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,12/18/2023,12/27/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,"During an incident a staff member pulled a child by their arms, as a form of redirection.","Operation submitted plan of compliance: 
Staff retrained during staff meeting on 11/30/23 on proper handling of children in care and CPI overview of the children . 
 
Please find the response below to the unannounced inspection that occurred on 11-21-2023. We will not be requesting an administrative review.

Standard/Rule	Specifics	Completion Date	Action Taken
748.507(1) Employee general responsibilities-Demonstrate competency, prudent judgment, self-control in presence of children and when performing assigned tasks.	During an incident a staff member pulled a child by their arms, as a form of redirection.
	11/30/2023	Program Administrator retrained all staff on how to properly redirect, guide, and handle the residents at Habilitative Homes during incidents and transitioning. The staff were retrained on not pulling the children by the arms and to lift then from under the armpits with their arms (inner forearms or where the elbow crease is) providing more support to child when getting them to a standing position. The staff were also retrained on guiding the children down to the floor during any incidents or transitions in which children drop to the floor supporting their drop; including lifting them from under the armpit with their arms (inner forearms or where the elbow crease is) to assist them back onto their feet.

Documentation of this training will be made available upon review or request.
			
"
