04/05/2022,748.2151(b)(1) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,04/19/2022,04/07/2022,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Three medication logs were not updated with medication administered in required timeframe.  ,"

The following response on how the facility will come into compliance was sent to Inspector by Administrator, Ms. Davis:  
1.	All staff will be trained on medication administration and documentation on 4/12/2022. Any staff unable to attend the training will be trained no later than 4/15/2022. 
2.	Supervisors and Management will request documentation monthly regarding medication administration from the school and upload to the childs file within the timeline set forth by minimum standards. 
3.	All medication logs will be reviewed by Shift Supervisors and the Program Supervisor daily to ensure compliance. 
4.	Shift Supervisor(s) and Program Supervisor will ensure all procedures regarding medication administration and documentation are followed, implemented appropriately by Direct Support Professionals, and compliance is maintained. The Program Manager will also conduct random audits of medication logs to ensure compliance.  
