11/23/2020,748.2151(c)(5) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/30/2020,11/30/2020,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,Medication record in child file was not up to date. The pill count had 10 and there was only 8 pills left. Staff had not documented last date and time given. ,"Letter will serve as a corrective action to the finding on 11/23/2020 which was cited during an unannounced monitoring inspection. 

748.2151 (c)(5) Medication record must included the date (day/month/year)and time each medication was administered. 

Response: The staff that was responsible for the medication error was counseled on medication administration and given a corrective action for failure to document medication administration accurately. All staff received re-training on the 5 rights of medication administration. Additionally we have implemented an additional medication count;there will now be one completed during each day and overnight shift. These will be documented on the daily inspection from which is completed each shift by the designed supervisory staff. "
